From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tsf-sync contributors <tsf-sync@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: add mt7925 tsf_set debugfs for write-path diagnosis

Patch 0005 established that mt792x_get_tsf returns 0 on mt7925 because
the MT_LPON_UTTR0/UTTR1 TSF mirror is not populated by firmware, even
though the preceding MT_LPON_TCR SW_MODE latch writeback succeeds. We
have only exercised the read path; the question of whether the write
path (MT_LPON_UTTR0/UTTR1 write followed by MT_LPON_TCR SW_WRITE latch
to push values into the on-chip TSF counter) works is still open. This
distinction is decisive:

  - If set_tsf works on mt7925, hardware-level TSF alignment is still
    achievable on this chip with an alternative read source.
  - If set_tsf is also dead, no approach we have considered can produce
    on-air TSF coordination on mt7925.

Add a write-only debugfs file phyN/mt76/tsf_set. Writing a decimal
u64 invokes mt792x_set_tsf on every active vif via the same mac80211
ops path the PTP glue uses. The file is strictly diagnostic -- no
behaviour changes, no module params, no init-time cost, and is
complementary to patch 0005's tsf_probe.

Intended test procedure (manual):
  1. Bring up an AP vif on a target mt7925 phy.
  2. Capture a beacon from the target BSSID from an independent
     observer (an Intel AX210 on the same host, or an off-rig laptop
     in monitor mode). Record the beacon's TSF timestamp field.
  3. echo 99999999999999 > /sys/kernel/debug/ieee80211/phyN/mt76/tsf_set
  4. Capture beacons again within one beacon interval.
  5. Compare. A jump of ~99999999999999 microseconds indicates the
     write path reaches the on-chip TSF. No change indicates the
     write path is also dead silicon.

Signed-off-by: tsf-sync contributors <tsf-sync@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7925/debugfs.c | 42 +++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 42 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7925/debugfs.c b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7925/debugfs.c
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7925/debugfs.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7925/debugfs.c
@@ -340,6 +340,41 @@ static int mt7925_tsf_probe_show(struct seq_file *s, void *data)
 	return 0;
 }
 
+/*
+ * TSF set -- invokes mt792x_set_tsf on every active vif with the
+ * user-supplied u64 value. Bare-minimum diagnostic companion to
+ * tsf_probe; observe effect on-air via an independent beacon capture
+ * (radiotap TSFT or the beacon-body timestamp field). No behaviour
+ * change to production code paths.
+ *
+ * Usage: echo <decimal u64> > /sys/kernel/debug/ieee80211/phyN/mt76/tsf_set
+ */
+struct mt7925_tsf_set_ctx {
+	struct mt792x_dev *dev;
+	u64 tsf;
+};
+
+static void mt7925_tsf_set_iter(void *data, u8 *mac,
+				struct ieee80211_vif *vif)
+{
+	struct mt7925_tsf_set_ctx *ctx = data;
+
+	mt792x_set_tsf(ctx->dev->mt76.hw, vif, ctx->tsf);
+}
+
+static int mt7925_tsf_set(void *data, u64 val)
+{
+	struct mt792x_dev *dev = data;
+	struct mt7925_tsf_set_ctx ctx = { .dev = dev, .tsf = val };
+
+	ieee80211_iterate_active_interfaces(dev->mt76.hw,
+					    IEEE80211_IFACE_ITER_RESUME_ALL,
+					    mt7925_tsf_set_iter, &ctx);
+	return 0;
+}
+
+DEFINE_DEBUGFS_ATTRIBUTE(fops_tsf_set, NULL, mt7925_tsf_set, "%llu\n");
+
 int mt7925_init_debugfs(struct mt792x_dev *dev)
 {
 	struct dentry *dir;
@@ -371,6 +406,7 @@ int mt7925_init_debugfs(struct mt792x_dev *dev)
 	debugfs_create_file("deep-sleep", 0600, dir, dev, &fops_ds);
 	debugfs_create_devm_seqfile(dev->mt76.dev, "tsf_probe", dir,
 				    mt7925_tsf_probe_show);
+	debugfs_create_file("tsf_set", 0200, dir, dev, &fops_tsf_set);
 
 	return 0;
 }
